<body>
<p>The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Networking servi ce  is a virtual networking service that
      leverages the OpenStack Neutron service to provide network connectivity and addressing to HP
      Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade devices.</p>
<p>The Networking service also provides an API to configure and manage a variety of network services.</p>
<p>You can use the Networking service to connect guest servers or you can define and configure your own virtual network topology.</p>
<section id="working-with-the-networking-service"> <title>Working with the Networking service</title>
<p>To perform tasks using the Networking service, you can use the dashboard, API or CLI.</p>
</section>
<section id="UI"> <title>Using the dashboards</title>
<p>You can use <xref
          href="../../CarrierGrade/AdminGuideNew/Dashboard/carrier-grade.dashboard.how-works.dita"
          >HP Helion Dashboard</xref>  to work with the Networking service.</p>
</section>
<section id="API"> <title>Using the API</title>
<p>You can use a low-level, raw REST API to access the Networking service. See the <xref href="http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-networking-v2.html" scope="external" format="html" >OpenStack Networking API v2.0 Reference</xref>.</p>
</section>
<section id="cli"> <title>Using the CLI</title>
<p>You can use any of several command-line interface software to access the Networking service. See
        the <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/cli-reference/content/neutronclient_commands.html"
          scope="external" format="html">OpenStack Command Line Interface Reference</xref>.</p>
<p>For more information on installing the CLI, see <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/user-guide/content/install_clients.html" scope="external" format="html" >Install the OpenStack command-line clients</xref>.</p>
